    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of large, deciduous, coniferous larch native to the Alps, Carpathians, and lowlands of northern Poland and southern Lithuania. It is cultivated for tough and durable timber, Venetian turpentine, and bark, which is used in tanning.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
